      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis experimental comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Mean relative error 8.3%; all predictions within ±15% of measured values. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all operating points. UQ campaign (Latin hypercube sampling, n=200) confirmed that inlet boundary condition uncertainty and fluid viscosity variation are the dominant contributors to output variance, accounting for 71% of total output spread. Sensitivity indices documented in the accompanying validation report appendix."
